/*Write a method called distance that accepts four integer coordinates x1, y1, x2, and y2 as parameters and
computes the distance between points (x1, y1) and (x2, y2) on the Cartesian plane.

For example, the call of distance(1, 0, 4, 4) would return 5.0 and the call of distance(10, 2, 3, 5) 
would return 7.615773105863909.
*/

public static double distance(int x1, int y1, int x2, int y2){
    double xDifference = Math.pow(x2 - x1, 2);
    double yDifference = Math.pow(y2 - y1, 2);
    return Math.pow(xDifference + yDifference, 0.5);
}
